The paper deals with the design of a novel architecture for analog cancellation and digital beamforming in full duplex MIMO systems. This involves signal processing, communication theory, and network architecture, which are all covered by the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents computer simulation results, which fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories.
